                            <comment id="14074238" author="irisding" created="Fri, 25 Jul 2014 09:41:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According the discussion from &lt;a href=&quot;http://cxf.547215.n5.nabble.com/context-injection-through-setter-method-method-name-restriction-td5746712.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cxf.547215.n5.nabble.com/context-injection-through-setter-method-method-name-restriction-td5746712.html&lt;/a&gt;, Let&apos;s relax the method name restriction and add a check for the parameterType as Interface&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Yes, 1. can be implemented as part the JIRA you created (the proxy won&apos;t &lt;br/&gt;
be created for non interfaces either way but no point in even trying to &lt;br/&gt;
do it). )&lt;/p&gt;

