                            <comment id="14077629" author="ashakirin" created="Tue, 29 Jul 2014 11:34:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Iris, &lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for the patch. I have applied it with two small changes: &lt;br/&gt;
a) set prefix is already checked into findContextSetterMethods(), therefore I removed it from checkContextMethod.&lt;br/&gt;
b) set with standard context classes is introduced, in order to warn user about injection of custom context requiring to register ContextProvider.&lt;/p&gt;

